SIMPLE: cosignitary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cosignitary
<hw>Co*sig"ni*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(k?-s?g"n?-t?-r?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>co-</ets> + <ets>sign</ets>. Cf.
<er>Signatory</er>.]</ety> <def>Signing some important public document
with another or with others; <as>as, a treaty violated by one of the
<ex>cosignitary</ex> powers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cosignitary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cosignitary
<hw>Co*sig"ni*ta*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Cosignitaries</plw> <pr>(-r<?/z)</pr>.</plu> <def>One who signs a
treaty or public document along with others or another; <as>as, the
<ex>cosignitaries</ex> of the treaty of Berlin</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cosily</ent>⟦br⟧
